celery/celery#10205.body:
****Description****

We are running a Celery worker with Redis as the broker. When the Redis connection is reset (for example by network interruption or Redis closing idle connections), Celery logs that the broker connection was lost and that it is trying to reconnect.

However, after this happens the worker stops consuming tasks from Redis and does not recover automatically. Tasks remain in the queue until the worker process/container is restarted.

We expected Celery to automatically reconnect to the Redis broker and resume consuming tasks. Previously also we faced this type issue and in the documentation it mentioned that broker connection issues has been fixed in latest version so we updated the celery version last month. 2 days back again faced the same issue. 

**Celery** : 5.5.0

**Python** : 3.10.19

Celery connection Config - 
`celery_app = Celery('CeleryMain', broker="redis://default:<password>=@prod.redis.cache.windows.net:6379/0")`

